First Lady Melania Trump joined her husband in Japan, where they visited Yokota Air Base to thank members of the military. She then had tea with Mrs. Abe and participated in a cultural presentation on the pearl industry. They ended the day with a private dinner with Prime Minister and Mrs. Abe. On the second day, Melania attended a business leaders event at the U.S. Embassy and a meet-and-greet with the families of embassy workers. They also met with Emperor Akihito and Empress Michiko at the Imperial Palace, followed by an Honor Guard Ceremony. Melania and Mrs. Abe visited a local school and received a calligraphy lesson. They then had lunch at Akasaka Palace before attending a meeting with families of Japanese citizens abducted by North Korea. Melania also attended a joint press conference with her husband and Prime Minister Abe. The day ended with a state banquet at Akasaka Palace. Melania expressed her enjoyment of the visit and thanked Prime Minister and Mrs. Abe for their hospitality.